# UI and UX Standards

## Product visual system

- Follow LoBoost dark-first palette and lime accent from `docs/design/DESIGN.md`.
- Keep interactions mobile-first and readable on small screens.
- Use accent color selectively for primary actions and high-signal states.

## Composition guidance

- Reuse existing product components/patterns before creating new ones.
- Keep navigation and layout behavior consistent per route group.
- Respect current implementation style used in each surface; avoid style-system thrash.

## Accessibility and clarity

- Keep labels and CTA text explicit and action-oriented.
- Ensure contrast and disabled/loading states are obvious.
- Avoid interaction dead-ends; provide clear back/cancel/retry paths.

## Motion and feedback

- Use subtle transitions for state changes.
- Prioritize performance and clarity over decorative animation.
